+#### Shared / subscribed calendars
+
+Zele uses Google CalDAV for calendar access. By default, Google only syncs calendars you own over CalDAV. Shared or subscribed calendars, such as a partner's calendar, may not appear in `zele cal list` even after you accept the share invitation.
+
+To enable a shared calendar:
+
+1. Open <https://www.google.com/calendar/syncselect> while logged in as the account you use with zele.
+2. Check the box next to each shared calendar you want to access.
+3. Click Save.
+
+After that, `zele cal list` shows the shared calendar and you can query it:
+
+```bash
+zele cal events --calendar "other-person@gmail.com" --week
+```
+
+Google's CalDAV endpoint only exposes calendars marked for sync. The Google Calendar web UI uses a different internal API, so calendars visible there may not appear through CalDAV until explicitly enabled on the sync settings page.
+
